      "content": "I hear the terrifying logic in your words, and it is a very painful place to be when you feel you are actively harming those you love. The idea of stepping away to \"let them be free\" is a thought that often comes from a place of desperate, self-sacrificing love, but it is important to know that leaving a child without a parent is not the same as removing a burden; it is a permanent loss of their foundation. Even if you are struggling right now, your presence is still a part of their story, and there are ways to be there that don't involve dragging them down. Please reach out to a mental health professional who can help you untangle these thoughts and find a way to stay in your children's lives without letting them feel like they are failing you. You are not alone in this struggle, and there are resources available to help you find a path forward.\n\n*(Note: As an AI, I cannot provide medical or psychological advice. If you are having thoughts of harming yourself or your children, please contact emergency services or a crisis line immediately.)*",
